    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-10-07T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-10-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <head>221. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission at the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d221fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 320/10–760. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1960-10-07T20:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 7, 1960—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>926. U.S. initiative re Soviet actions in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                        (<gloss target="#t_TOSEC1">Tosec</gloss> 49).<note n="2" xml:id="d221fn2">
                        <ref target="#d196">Document 196</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>In my opinion <persName corresp="#p_KNS2">Khrushchev</persName> has
                        overplayed his hand with neutralists and others here both through his bitter
                        attacks against U.S., through his attacks on <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                            >SYG</gloss>, and his personal behavior in plenary hall when <persName
                            corresp="#p_MHS2">Macmillan</persName> spoke.<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d221fn3">See <ref target="#d198">Document 198</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>There is prevailing sentiment in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> against
                        cold-war atmosphere and Soviets are suffering for having made such attacks
                        basis their posture in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>.</item>
                    <pb facs="0438" n="408" xml:id="pg_408"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>In these circumstances I do not think we should submit item of nature
                        contained <gloss target="#t_REFTEL1">reftel</gloss>. We will have ample
                        opportunity in rebuttal to Soviet items and charges to include in speeches
                        and possibly even resolutions main elements contained in draft memorandum of
                        explanation. I believe this is way in which we will be most effective this
                        year.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_WJJ2">Wadsworth</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
